<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1294722>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. MorPhology of the sPecies of Pediobius: A, P. arcuatus Kerrich, habitus of the female; B, P. bruchicida (Rondani) (head and mesosoma, lateral vieW, SEM); C, P. imbreus walker (tyPe sPecies of Pediobius), ProPodeum, SEM; D–F, P. derroni Bouček, SEM: D, face; E, ProPodeum; F, loWer face (md, mandible)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1294722/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1294736>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Pediobius afroteres. A–D, head and anterior Part of mesosoma (holotyPe, South Africa, SAMC): A, dorsal vieW; C, fronto-lateral vieW; B, D, frontal vieW; E, F, ParatyPes, lateral vieW (Kenya, reared from coffee berries, BMNH): E, female, F, male." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1294736/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1294738>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Pediobius afroteres, SEM. A–C, ParatyPe female (Kenya, reared from coffee berries, BMNH): A, head in frontal vieW, B, C, lateral vieW (B, habitus, C, head, mesosoma and base of metasoma); D, E, ParatyPe males: D, head in lateral vieW (South Africa, SANC), E, head, mesosoma and base of metasoma (Kenya, reared from coffee berries, BMNH)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1294738/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1294742>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Pediobius askari. A–D, holotyPe female (South Africa, BMNH), E, ParatyPe female (Tanzania, SAMC). A, B, habitus: A, dorsal vieW, B, lateral vieW; C, D, head and anterior Part of mesosoma: C, fronto-lateral vieW, D, dorsal vieW; E, head, mesosoma and anterior Part of metasoma in dorso-lateral vieW." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1294742/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1294744>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Pediobius askari, ParatyPe female (ZimbabWe, BMNH), SEM. A, B, head, mesosoma and anterior Part of metasoma: A, ventro-lateral vieW, B, dorso-lateral vieW; C, head in frontal vieW; D, mouth oPening and mandibles; E, ProPodeum and Petiole in lateral vieW; F, head in dorso-lateral vieW." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1294744/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1294746>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Pediobius maleficus. A–C, holotyPe female (DRC, RMCA): A, B, habitus: A, dorsal vieW, B, lateral vieW; C, head and mesosoma in dorsal vieW; D–F, ParatyPes: D, E, male (Gabon, SAMC), F, female (DRC, RMCA); D, head and anterior Part of mesosoma in dorsal vieW; E, F, head in frontal vieW." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1294746/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1294724>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. A–C, Pediobius sPP.: A–C, formerly classified in Rhynchentedon, D–E, formerly classified in Pediobomyia. A, P. achterbergi (Malaysia); B–C, P. maximus (SingaPore): B, head in frontal vieW With mouth oPening and mandibles in inset; C, mesosoma and anterior Part of metasoma of the holotyPe (BMNH); D, E, P. darwini (Australia): D, head, mesosoma and anterior Part of metasoma in lateral vieW, E, loWer face and mandible in lateral vieW." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1294724/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1294754>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Pediobius sPP. A–D, Posterior Part of mesosoma and anterior Part of metasoma in dorsal vieW." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1294754/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1294726>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Myrmokata diparoides (DRC): A, B, head, mesosoma and anterior Part of metasoma: A, lateral vieW, B, dorsal vieW; C, head and anterior Part of mesosoma, vieWed under angle; D, face; E, Posterior Part of mesosoma, ProPodeum and anterior Part of metasoma With tiny scutellar seta arroWed in inset." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1294726/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1294752>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Pediobius sPP. A–D, head in frontal vieW; E–H, head and anterior Part of mesosoma in dorsal vieW." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1294752/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

